[src:containers-vs-vms/full-virtualization] It thus included such elements as an instruction set, main memory, interrupts, exceptions, and device access.
[src:containers-vs-vms/full-virtualization] The result was a single machine that could be multiplexed among many users.
[src:containers-vs-vms/full-virtualization] Hardware-assisted virtualization first appeared on the IBM System/370 in 1972, for use with VM/370, the first virtual machine operating system.
