[src:containers-vs-vms/full-virtualization] A common goal of virtualization is to centralize administrative tasks while improving scalability and overall hardware-resource utilization.
[src:containers-vs-vms/full-virtualization] With virtualization, several operating systems can be run in parallel on a single central processing unit (CPU).
